cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper focuses on attacking face recognition networks using a generative network with attention modules and a conditional variational autoencoder. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of adversarial attacks and the competition between generator and discriminator suggest that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the security implications of these attacks, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of generated face images suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
